  -> iter-45-position-independent-arg-scan-by-topology-name
  => "Patch: empirical_anchor_v2.hexa main parser (line 485-525)"
  => "Algorithm:"
  => "  1. Scan _e2args for first arg whose _e2topo_id() returns ≥ 0"
  => "  2. That is the topology arg at idx i"
  => "  3. Read ticks from args[i-1] (with int parse fallback)"
  => "  4. Read seed from args[i+1] (with int parse fallback)"
  => "  5. Fallback to legacy hardcoded args[2/3/4] if no topology found"
  => "Effect: CLI grammar 'hexa run ...hexa <ticks> <topology> <seed>' now works"
  => "        on BOTH local hexa --selftest AND hetzner remote run"

