@R clay-iter-51-entropy-formula :: meta [4]
  => "Bipartite entanglement entropy proxy implementation:"
  => "  S_proxy = 4 p (1 - p) per-mille scale [0, 1000]"
  => "  where p = qs_half_cut_weight() / 1000 (bipartition probability)"
  => "  peaks at p=500 (max entropy = 1000 = ln(2) bits effectively)"
  => "  drops to 0 at p=0 or p=1000 (separable state, no entanglement)"
  => "Why this proxy:"
  => "  Hexa-lang has no native log function (would need Taylor series)"
  => "  4p(1-p) approximates H(p)=−p log₂(p)−(1−p) log₂(1−p) within 10%"
  => "  Exact formula: S_vN = -Σ λᵢ log λᵢ over Schmidt eigenvalues"
  => "  Schmidt-decomp computation requires SVD — heavy for integer arithmetic"
  => "  raw 91 C3: this is a PROXY, not exact von Neumann entropy"

