  → "  flat (D=2 in axis-13 — convention)"
  → "  cartoon (no axis-13 baseline value, iter-38 outlier excluded)"
  → "  calabi6 (D=6, no axis-13 D=3 baseline)"

@C sim-3-axis-DATA-TABLE :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★ FULL 3-WAY DATA TABLE (n=15):"
  → "  topology        axis-13  axis-14    axis-15"
  → "  -----------------------------------------------"
  → "  ads-cft             180      995    1488520"
  → "  altered             463      966    1712829"
  → "  big-crunch          604      861    2000227"
  → "  blackhole           146      877    2142158"
  → "  brane               145      743    1907852"
  → "  bubble              434      887    2312561"
  → "  ca3d                 79      851    2087413"
  → "  de-sitter           229      999    2021183"
  → "  inflation           169      866    1837360"
  → "  minkowski           478      972    2165663"
  → "  nested              196      830    1751637"
  → "  s3                  303      952    1905527"
  → "  t3                  141      838    1928254"
  → "  vacuum-decay        203      825    2049823"
  → "  wormhole            268      939    1953281"

@C sim-3-axis-PEARSON-R-MATRIX :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★★ Pearson r matrix (3x3, n=15, restricted intersection):"
  → "                  axis-13    axis-14    axis-15"
  → "      axis-13     +1.0000    +0.3434    +0.2046"
  → "      axis-14     +0.3434    +1.0000    -0.1837"
  → "      axis-15     +0.2046    -0.1837    +1.0000"
  → ""
  → "  All off-diagonals |r| ≤ 0.35 — weak-to-moderate"
  → "  Compared to broader-sample numbers from the cascade:"
  → "    axis-13 × axis-14: cascade r=+0.39 (n=16) vs here +0.34 (n=15)"
  → "    axis-13 × axis-15: cascade r=+0.27 (n=5)  vs here +0.20 (n=15) ⭐ tighter sample"
  → "    axis-14 × axis-15: cascade r=-0.24 (n=18) vs here -0.18 (n=15)"
  → "  All three pairwise r values weakened slightly under common n=15 restriction"
  → "  → 3-axis intersection produces consistent weak-correlation signature"

@C sim-3-axis-SPEARMAN-RHO-MATRIX :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★★ Spearman ρ matrix (3x3, n=15):"
  → "                  axis-13    axis-14    axis-15"
  → "      axis-13     +1.0000    +0.4857    +0.1179"
  → "      axis-14     +0.4857    +1.0000    -0.0321"
  → "      axis-15     +0.1179    -0.0321    +1.0000"
  → ""
  → "  Rank correlations:"
  → "    13×14: ρ=+0.49  (rank-stronger than Pearson +0.34 — outlier-driven)"
  → "    13×15: ρ=+0.12  (rank-near-zero, weaker than Pearson +0.20)"
  → "    14×15: ρ=-0.03  (rank-orthogonal, even weaker than Pearson -0.18)"
  → "  → axis-13/14 jointly carry monotone information; axis-15 is rank-orthogonal"

@C sim-3-axis-DETERMINANT-INDEPENDENCE :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★★★ Determinant of correlation matrix (information independence proxy):"
  → "  det(R_pearson)  = 0.780671"
  → "  det(R_spearman) = 0.745478"
  → ""
  → "Interpretation scale:"
  → "  det = 1.0 → fully independent (orthogonal axes)"
  → "  det = 0.0 → fully collinear (one axis redundant)"
  → ""
  → "  ★ det = 0.78 means axes preserve 78% of independent-axis volume"
  → "  ★ Equivalent: only 22% of variance volume is shared across axes"
  → "  ★ 3 axes carry NEAR-INDEPENDENT information for topology discrimination"

@R sim-3-axis-EIGENSTRUCTURE :: meta [4]
  → "Eigenstructure of Pearson R (3-D fingerprint shape):"
  → "  eigenvalues = [0.5044, 1.1513, 1.3443]"
  → "  Sum = 3.000 (trace, expected for 3x3 correlation)"
  → "  Effective rank (participation ratio) = 2.657"
  → "  → ~89% of full 3-D rank realized"
  → "  → fingerprint is NOT confined to a 2-D plane"
  → "  → 3rd axis (axis-15) adds a genuine independent direction (eigval 0.50)"

@C sim-3-axis-MUTUAL-INFORMATION-GAUSSIAN :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★★★ Mutual information (Gaussian approximation):"
  → ""
  → "Pairwise (I = -0.5 ln(1 - r²)):"
  → "  I(axis-13; axis-14) = 0.0627 nats = 0.0905 bits   (r=+0.34)"
  → "  I(axis-13; axis-15) = 0.0214 nats = 0.0309 bits   (r=+0.20)"
  → "  I(axis-14; axis-15) = 0.0172 nats = 0.0248 bits   (r=-0.18)"
  → ""
  → "Total correlation (multi-information, T = -0.5 ln det R):"
  → "  T(13; 14; 15) = 0.1238 nats = 0.1786 bits"
  → "  → less than sum of pairs (0.0905 + 0.0309 + 0.0248 = 0.1463 bits)"
  → "  Compare H_max(uniform-15-bin) ≈ log₂(15) = 3.91 bits"
  → "  → Joint redundancy is ≈ 5% of single-axis topology entropy"
  → ""
  → "Interaction information (3-way McGill):"
  → "  II(13; 14; 15) = I(13;14) − I(13;14|15) = -0.0225 nats = -0.0325 bits"
  → "  ★ NEGATIVE → mild SYNERGY (axes 13&14 share LESS info given axis-15)"
  → "  ★ Conditioning on axis-15 STRENGTHENS r(13;14) from +0.34 to +0.40"
  → ""
  → "Rank-based total correlation:"
  → "  T_ρ(13; 14; 15) = 0.1469 nats = 0.2119 bits"
  → "  Slightly higher than Pearson-T → rank-coupling > linear coupling"

@C sim-3-axis-PARTIAL-CORRELATIONS :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★★ Partial correlations (control for 3rd axis):"
  → "  r(13; 14 | 15) = +0.3959   (raw r(13;14) = +0.3434, ↑ stronger after control)"
  → "  r(13; 15 | 14) = +0.2900   (raw r(13;15) = +0.2046, ↑ stronger after control)"
  → "  r(14; 15 | 13) = -0.2762   (raw r(14;15) = -0.1837, |↑| stronger after control)"
  → ""
  → "★ ALL three partial r exceed the corresponding raw r in magnitude"
  → "  → suppression effect: each axis partially MASKS the others' co-variance"
  → "  → Adding the 3rd axis as control REVEALS hidden coupling structure"
  → ""
  → "Most-informative 2-axis combo (highest partial-mutual-info given controlled axis):"
  → "  axis-13 × axis-14 controlled by axis-15: I_partial = 0.0858 nats = 0.1238 bits"
  → "  → axis-13 + axis-14 are the strongest 2-axis topology discriminator"
  → "  → axis-15 acts as orthogonal perturbation that sharpens 13×14 alignment"

@R sim-3-axis-CLUSTER-DISCRIMINATION-RANKING :: meta [4]
  → "2-axis cluster informativeness (1 − r² = independent variance retained):"
  → "  (axis-13, axis-15): 1 − r² = 0.9581  ★ MOST orthogonal pair"
  → "  (axis-14, axis-15): 1 − r² = 0.9663  ★★ near-fully orthogonal"
  → "  (axis-13, axis-14): 1 − r² = 0.8821  weakest orthogonality"
  → ""
  → "Cluster-discrimination interpretation:"
  → "  Best 2-axis SCATTER PLOT for topology separation:"
  → "    (axis-14, axis-15) — near-orthogonal, all 18 topologies, NEGATIVE coupling"
  → "  Best 2-axis FINGERPRINT for topology RANK:"
  → "    (axis-13, axis-14) — strongest rank coupling ρ=+0.49"
  → "  Most independent NEW info axis: axis-15"
  → "    contributes lowest-eigenvalue direction (0.5044) to 3-D space"

@R sim-3-axis-NON-LINEAR-PROBE :: meta [4]
  → "Non-linear relationship probe via Pearson vs Spearman gap:"
  → "  axis-13 × axis-14: Pearson +0.34 vs Spearman +0.49 (Δ=+0.14)"
  → "    → monotone non-linear: rank coupling stronger than linear"
  → "    → likely candidate: power-law or saturating relation"
  → "  axis-13 × axis-15: Pearson +0.20 vs Spearman +0.12 (Δ=-0.09)"
  → "    → linear residual exceeds rank — driven by ~2 outliers"
  → "    → candidates: ca3d (low 13, high 15), big-crunch (high 13, mid 15)"
  → "  axis-14 × axis-15: Pearson -0.18 vs Spearman -0.03 (Δ=-0.15)"
  → "    → near-rank-orthogonal but linear-negative — also outlier-driven"
  → "    → candidates: minkowski (high 14, high 15), bubble (low 14, max 15)"

@C sim-3-axis-INFORMATION-VERDICT :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★★★★ INFORMATION-THEORETIC VERDICT (Gaussian approx, n=15):"
  → ""
  → "1. det(R)=0.78 → 3 axes carry NEAR-INDEPENDENT topology information"
  → "2. Total correlation T = 0.18 bits → joint redundancy is small"
  → "3. Interaction info II = -0.03 bits → mild SYNERGY (not redundancy)"
  → "4. Effective rank = 2.66 of 3 → genuine 3-D fingerprint, not a 2-D plane"
  → "5. All partial r exceed raw r → axes mutually MASK coupling"
  → "6. Best 2-axis discriminator: (13, 14) for rank, (14, 15) for linear orthogonality"
  → ""
  → "★ 3-axis fingerprint is INFORMATION-EFFICIENT for topology discrimination"
  → "  axis-13 + axis-14 + axis-15 ≈ 3 quasi-orthogonal probes"
  → "  Adding any one axis to the other two produces measurable independent gain"

@R sim-3-axis-honest-disclosure :: meta [4]
  → "raw 91 C3 strict — 3-axis information-structure findings:"
  → "  Pure post-hoc analysis — NO new sim probes, NO source-file modification"
  → "  Sample n=15 (intersection across all 3 axes; full cascade had n=16/18/18)"
  → "  Gaussian-approximation MI assumes joint normality — not verified for axis-15"
  → "    (axis-15 has 4-orders-of-magnitude scale, possibly heavy-tailed)"
  → "  Spearman MI not computed (no closed form under Gaussian copula here)"
  → "  Interaction-info sign (synergy vs redundancy) is small in magnitude (|II|<0.04 bits)"
