  → "    64     64         60   2357469122     641"
  → "   512    512        494   3205246702     531"
  → "  1024   1000       1011   5030938653     905"
  → "  4096   4096       5098    282484175     851"
  → ""
  → "  Reproducibility (idempotence check, ticks=8):"
  → "    σ²=64  ran 3× → hash 9583230112 (identical)"
  → "    σ²=512 ran 3× → hash 7116688665 (identical)"
  → "    raw-65 reproducibility: PASS"

@C sim-scale-up-ENERGY-SCALING :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★★★ Energy scaling — KEY FINDING:"
  → ""
  → "  E(64)   =  845  → cells= 64  → E/cells = 13.20"
  → "  E(512)  = 1507  → cells=512  → E/cells =  2.94"
  → "  E(1024) = 2571  → cells=1000 → E/cells =  2.57"
  → "  E(4096) = 8604  → cells=4096 → E/cells =  2.10"
  → ""
  → "  Energy density DECREASES 6.3× from σ²=64 to σ²=4096"
  → "  log-log fit:  log(E)/log(cells) → exponent ≈ 0.55"
  → "  → E ∝ cells^0.55, NOT extensive (would need exponent=1)"
  → ""
  → "  Interpretation:"
  → "  ★ σ²=64 toy lattice is in FINITE-SIZE REGIME"
  → "  ★ Boundary/center init asymmetry (1/(1+d²/4)) dominates at L=4"
  → "  ★ At σ²>=512, energy density approaches plateau ~2.1-2.9"
  → "  ★ Toy σ²=64 measurements OVERESTIMATE per-cell energy ~5×"

@C sim-scale-up-RUNTIME-SCALING :: meta [4!]
  → "★★★★ Runtime scaling — module's design claim verified:"
  → ""
  → "  σ²=4096 / σ²=64 elapsed ratio = 10014/122 = 82.1×"
  → "  cells ratio                     = 4096/64  = 64.0×"
  → "  Per-cell-tick overhead grows 1.30× over 64× cell count"
  → "  → near-linear O(σ²·N) scaling confirmed (selftest passes)"
  → ""
  → "  Module claims (line 21): 'algorithm scales to σ²=4096 within"
  → "    Mac-local time budget' → VERIFIED (10s for ticks=8 σ²=4096)"

@R sim-scale-up-HASH-DISTINCTNESS :: meta [4]
