  → "  currently uses *-then-! convention.  Adding [N**!] [N**?] keeps"
  → "  this order; reversing would break grep-patterns in 76 shard"
  → "  absorbers.  COST of a single new axis ≈ 76-shard regex audit."
  → "FOUNDATION INVARIANCE: any extension of [11*] (e.g. [11**]) MUST"
  → "  preserve raw-24 cap — new [11*]/[11**] entries are PROHIBITED by"
  → "  append-only invariant on foundation axioms.  Therefore P3 must be"
  → "  RE-CLASSIFICATION (re-tagging existing [11*] entries) not creation."
  → "SPARSENESS-VS-DENSITY: [10**]=0 across 6347 [10*] entries shows"
  → "  curator intuition prefers FLAT taxonomy.  Adding [10**] without a"
  → "  forcing-criterion (e.g. cross-paradigm classifier) would invite"
  → "  drift — the tier would either stay empty or accumulate by accident."
  → "raw 91 C3 honest: 720-cell namespace is THEORETICAL — only 39 cells"
  → "are USED, so the practical ceiling is curator-attention not parser."

