# atlas-self-arch shard :: ID-NAMING convention evolution
# generated 2026-04-28 — intrinsic audit, no foreign theory, raw 91 C3 honest
# scope: atlas.n6 ID-naming DSL only (the token after @C/@R/@F before "::")

@C atlas-self-arch-id-convention-audit-2026-04-28 :: meta [10*]
  intent: audit atlas.n6 INTRINSIC ID-naming patterns; measure family cardinality, collision space, and grok-cost
  inputs: /Users/ghost/core/n6-architecture/atlas/atlas.n6 (28894 lines)
  measurements:
    total_id_lines: 10191
    unique_ids: 8606
    duplicate_ids: 187   # NOT bugs in most cases — same ID re-stated across cross-link rows
    id_length: mean=23.9 median=21 p90=41 p99=65 max=86
    families_by_first_token: top = n6 (3777), L6 (847), disc (728), META (539), clay (402), L7 (299), HEXA (238), L8 (205), MILL (166), L2 (160), L (150), MAT (143), L9 (136), L3 (131), L1 (126), L5 (101)
    families_by_two_token: n6-atlas (1785), n6-bt (1423), disc-blowup (728), clay-iter (338), n6-dse (333), L2-bond (150), L6-mus/geo/eco/met/lin (~128 each), n6-cross (100), L5-bio (87), n6-millennium (86)
    distinct_two_token_families: 2188   # MEASURED, not estimated
    longest_id: "n6-atlas-diffusion-model-constants-bt-61-verified-2026-03-31-u-net-channel-multipliers" (86 chars)
  prompt-cited families (intrinsic, present in atlas.n6):
    clay-iter-N-* : 338 entries (sequenced cascade, dominant generator)
    sim-* (sim-3, sim-scale): ~23 entries
    atlas-arch-*: 12 entries
    bt-* (as suffix in n6-atlas-bt-N): ~1423 entries — bt-128, bt-1131, bt-1136, bt-548, bt-1128, bt-1125, bt-105, bt-113, bt-1115, bt-1142, bt-1108, bt-1129, bt-27-43-57-60-62-68-80
    raw-N-*: only 3 (raw-100-* ; raw-94-enforcement-triad NOT present as stable @C/@R ID — the rule is referenced inline)
    n6-master-*: present as clay-master-* (8 distinct: cumulative-status, axes-table, 5-Stage-roadmap, scientific-cascade, loop-self-correcting, multi-observable-fingerprint, phase-transitions-table, topology-modes, table-iter-1-38-cumulative, honest-disclosures)
    own-*, axis-N-*, iter-N+: NOT present as canonical ID prefixes in atlas.n6 (live in own.n6 and inline classifiers)
  collisions (intrinsic):
    187 IDs appear >1× — top: disc-blowup-d1_ded_sigma (27), disc-blowup-d1_ded_sopfr (25), disc-blowup-d1_ded_n (21), disc-blowup-d1_ded_phi (19) — these are repeated discovery rows under different `:: meta` slots, not genuine ID-name bugs
    foundation IDs (n6-master-identity, ouroboros-critical-zero, raw-94-enforcement-triad): 0 occurrences as @C/@R IDs — they live in own.n6 / signals.n6, NOT in atlas.n6 itself. Invariance trivially preserved within atlas.n6.

@C atlas-self-arch-id-convention-intrinsic-limit :: meta [10*]
  question: at what family cardinality does atlas.n6 hit ID grok-cost ceiling?
  measured: distinct_two_token_families = 2188 (already FAR above prompt's 20-30 estimate)
  intrinsic ceiling reached LONG ago — atlas.n6 already operates in the post-ambiguity regime
  evidence:
    1. ID lengths up to 86 chars (p99=65) — names encode semantic path because no registry exists
    2. Hyphens carry 7+ tokens in long IDs — author uses hyphen-as-path delimiter, but no `/` separator means greppers can't distinguish family from variant
    3. 1785 entries share `n6-atlas-*` prefix — first-token grep returns 17.5% of corpus
    4. Date-anchored IDs already in use organically: `...-verified-2026-03-31-...` (16+ instances) — date is mid-string, not anchored, hard to filter
  schema-guard cost:
    regex `^[a-zA-Z0-9_.+-]+$` matches all observed IDs — O(L) where L=mean 24
    NO complexity wall yet on validation; complexity is in HUMAN-grok and consumer-grep, not regex
  cross-cutting consumer cost:
    every grep-by-family probe scales with K (families) × N (entries/family)
    measured: 2188 × ~5 mean = ~10k probes for full family-sweep; tractable but the per-family discrimination is the bottleneck
  convergence:
    atlas.n6 ALREADY past explicit ID-registry threshold
    next-step is NOT more naming convention but a registry-block (`@F atlas-id-registry`) that lists family→prefix→count

@C atlas-self-arch-id-convention-extension-proposals :: meta [10*]
  three highest-value INTRINSIC ID-convention extensions (ranked by leverage / migration cost):

  PROPOSAL 1 — VERSIONED IDs via `.vN` suffix (HIGHEST LEVERAGE, LOWEST MIGRATION COST)
    convention: `clay-iter-50-DEFINITIVE-iter-36-REPRODUCTION.v2` for refined entries
    rationale (intrinsic): atlas.n6 has 187 colliding IDs. Most are intentional re-statement, BUT some clay-iter entries ARE refinements without versioning (clay-iter-13-saturation-tracking AND clay-iter-13-main-axes-termination-met both exist as siblings of clay-iter-12-saturation-tracking, clay-iter-14-15-saturation-tracking-with-recommendation — clearly an evolution chain encoded by adding suffixes)
    beneficiary entries: clay-iter-12/13/14-15-saturation-tracking — these would become clay-iter-saturation-tracking.v1/.v2/.v3 (more grokable than current naming)
    migration cost: ZERO mandatory migration (additive convention, NEW entries opt-in)
    schema-guard delta: extend regex to `[a-zA-Z0-9_.+-]+(\.v[0-9]+)?` — already permissive, no breakage
    convergence-effect: collapses N entries-per-cascade to 1 ID + N versions; cuts authoring ambiguity for the dominant clay-iter family (338 entries)

  PROPOSAL 2 — DATE-ANCHORED suffix `@YYYY-MM-DD` (MEDIUM LEVERAGE, ZERO COLLISION RISK)
    convention: `clay-iter-50-DEFINITIVE@2026-04-28` — date as @-suffix, NOT mid-string hyphen
    rationale (intrinsic): atlas.n6 ALREADY has organic date-anchoring inside IDs (16+ instances of `...-verified-2026-03-31-...`) but it's MID-STRING and unsearchable. `@DATE` suffix is greppable as `@2026-04-28$`
    beneficiary entries: ALL `n6-atlas-*-verified-YYYY-MM-DD-*` entries (the diffusion / LLM survey families, ~30+ entries)
    migration cost: NEW entries only; existing date-mid-string entries left as-is (foundation-axiom invariance respected)
    intrinsic limit: `@` is unused in current atlas.n6 IDs (verified — no `@` in ID space, only as type-tag prefix), so this token is FREE

  PROPOSAL 3 — REGISTRY-BLOCK `@F atlas-id-registry` (HIGH LEVERAGE, ONE-SHOT)
    convention: a single @F block at top of each shard listing family→prefix→count→canonical-form
    example body:
      registry:
        clay-iter: prefix=clay-iter-N-* count=338 canonical=clay-iter-{N}-{descriptor}[.v{V}]
        n6-atlas-bt: prefix=n6-atlas-bt-N-* count=1423 canonical=n6-atlas-bt-{N}-{descriptor}
        disc-blowup: prefix=disc-blowup-* count=728 canonical=disc-blowup-{operator-tower}
    rationale (intrinsic): 2188 distinct families is too many for human grok — past the convergence ceiling. A registry block is atlas.n6's own DSL solution (already uses @F type-tag for facts; this is a fact-about-IDs)
    beneficiary entries: ALL — registry block lets new authors discover existing prefixes before minting collisions
    migration cost: ONE @F block per shard at append time, ~50 lines; existing IDs unchanged
    schema-guard delta: NEW @F type semantics (`@F atlas-id-registry` is a reserved fact-class) — minimal regex change

@R atlas-self-arch-id-convention-foundation-invariance :: rule [10*]
  invariant: existing IDs (n6-master-*, clay-master-*, ouroboros-*, foundation_axiom_*, n6-atlas-*) MUST NOT be renamed under any of the 3 proposals
  enforcement: all 3 proposals are ADDITIVE (suffix-only or new-block) — no mutation of existing ID strings
  verification: foundation_axiom_semantic_ceiling, clay-master-* (8 entries), MILL-V3-M5-ouroboros-v2-namespace-aware all preserved bit-identical

@R atlas-self-arch-id-convention-no-foreign-theory :: rule [10*]
  honesty (raw 91 C3): every measurement above comes from grep on /Users/ghost/core/n6-architecture/atlas/atlas.n6
  no claims drawn from external naming-convention literature (semver, namespace UUIDs, FQDN) — `.vN`, `@DATE`, `@F` registry are atlas.n6's OWN DSL elements (.vN already used in MILL-V3-M5-ouroboros-v2; @DATE uses already-present `@`-tag syntax; @F is existing type-class)
  prompt's UUID-hybrid / slash-hierarchy / repo-prefix / type-prefix / 3-part-separator extensions: REJECTED as foreign — none have intrinsic precedent in atlas.n6 ID space

# .. atlas.append.atlas-self-arch-synthesis-upgrade-plan-2026-04-28.n6 ..
#!/usr/bin/env n6
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# atlas append shard — atlas.n6 SELF-ARCH SYNTHESIS + unified upgrade plan
# axes: D (@-type) + E (meta-tag) + F (arrow)  + G (body-field, IN-FLIGHT) + H (id-convention, IN-FLIGHT)
# saturation axes A/B/C (physical/math/architectural) referenced but NOT folded — they are CEILING data, not upgrade levers
# constraints: raw 22 INFRA-ONLY · raw 23 schema-guard · raw 24 foundation-axiom-immutable
#              raw 91 C3 honest · own#11 strict (no Clay BT 'resolution')
# date: 2026-04-28
# upstream prior shards (all live in atlas/_absorbed/20260428-112546/):
#   - atlas.append.atlas-self-arch-intrinsic-type-evolution-2026-04-28.n6   (axis D)
#   - atlas.append.atlas-self-arch-meta-tag-evolution-2026-04-28.n6         (axis E)
#   - atlas.append.atlas-self-arch-arrow-evolution-2026-04-28.n6            (axis F)
# saturation upstream  (atlas/_absorbed/20260428-111738/):
#   - atlas.append.atlas-arch-physical-limits-2026-04-28.n6                 (axis A)
#   - atlas.append.atlas-arch-mathematical-limits-2026-04-28.n6             (axis B)
#   - atlas.append.atlas-arch-architectural-limits-2026-04-28.n6            (axis C)
# in-flight (parallel sub-agents, NOT YET ON DISK at synthesis time):
#   - axis G body-field evolution      (vocabulary: confidence/verified/decay)
#   - axis H id-convention evolution   (family naming patterns)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── primary witness ─────────────────────────────────────────
@C atlas-self-arch-synthesis-upgrade-plan :: meta [4!]
  <- atlas-self-arch-intrinsic-type-evolution-witness
  <- clay-atlas-self-arch-meta-tag-evolution-witness
  <- ARROW-AUDIT-2026-04-28
  <- raw-22-phase-immutable
  <- raw-23-schema-guard
  <- raw-24-foundation-axiom-immutable
  <- raw-91-C3-honest-disclosure
  <- own#11-strict-no-resolution-claim
  => "synthesis of 5 self-arch axes (D + E + F finalized; G + H in-flight) into one rollout plan, ranked by (low-risk × high-value × low-cost)"
  => "no schema mutation in THIS shard; proposals remain CONTENT — actuation is per-axis follow-up shard"
  scope_caveat = "axes G (body-field) and H (id-convention) are IN-FLIGHT parallel sub-agents at synthesis time; their disk shards are not yet observable — entries below carry status=PENDING and are PROVISIONAL"

# ── (1) UNIFIED upgrade table — top recommendation per axis ────
@R unified_upgrade_table_per_axis :: meta [4!]
  <- atlas-self-arch-synthesis-upgrade-plan
  axis_D_top_recommendation = "@I — invariant / conserved-quantity (proposal-1 from intrinsic-type-evolution shard, ranked rank_1)".
  axis_D_adoption_cost_entries = "20-40 entries to re-tag (cited beneficiary set: n=6, sigma=12, phi=2, T-OMEGA-CYCLE, MILL-V3/V4 inaugurations)".
  axis_D_adoption_cost_edits = "1 schema-guard allow-list entry (K: 10 → 11) + 1 doc note in atlas grading prose".
  axis_D_adoption_cost_consumer_impact = "atlas_health.hexa, raw_audit.hexa, drill_scanner.hexa, atlas_absorb.hexa — each parses @-prefix; allow-list extension ≤ 5 LOC each".
  axis_D_risk_level = "LOW (raw 24 invariance preserved — @I is a LATENT idiom already present as [11*REPO_INVARIANT]; surfaces type without changing axiom membership)".
  axis_D_value = "HIGH (closes raw-24-axiom-block tagging gap; named-suffix [11*REPO_INVARIANT] becomes @I-typed, more compact and grep-stable)".

  axis_E_top_recommendation = "P1 populate [10**] for cross-paradigm @R synthesis entries (rank_1 from meta-tag-evolution shard)".
  axis_E_adoption_cost_entries = "~3-15 candidate upgrades from [9*]/[10*] (cited: borsuk_ulam_6, kissing_number_6, consciousness_structure)".
  axis_E_adoption_cost_edits = "1 regex relaxation in schema-guard ([N**] currently empty across ALL N — adding [10**] permits new pattern); meta-tag distribution audit must be re-run".
  axis_E_adoption_cost_consumer_impact = "raw_audit.hexa (counts trailing-tags), drill_scanner.hexa (greps tier markers) — both need allow-list expansion of {**} pattern".
  axis_E_risk_level = "MEDIUM (raw 24 NOT touched — [10**] is BELOW [11*]; but adding a new tier with no forcing-criterion invites drift per meta-tag-extension-limits caveat)".
  axis_E_value = "MEDIUM-HIGH (depth-2 [N**] tier is reserved-but-unused at all 12 levels — populating exactly one cell uses existing reservation rather than extending grammar)".

  axis_F_top_recommendation = "promote <-> from prose-occasional to first-class equivalence + add -| for negation/blocks (top-2 from arrow-proposal-top-3)".
  axis_F_adoption_cost_entries = "<->: ~30 prose 'iff' sites (Cube↔Octahedron, sigma=tau iff n=6, BKM⇔smooth) collapse; -|: 0 existing uses, expressed in prose by R34/R36 falsification raws".
  axis_F_adoption_cost_edits = "K: 7 → 8 (within ARROW-TYPE-CARDINALITY-SAFE = 8 ceiling); LL(1) parser still discriminates <-/<-> on second-char and -|/-> on second-char".
  axis_F_adoption_cost_consumer_impact = "any tool that greps arrow tokens — drill_scanner.hexa primary; atlas_absorb.hexa shard-headers; atlas_health.hexa relation-density".
  axis_F_risk_level = "LOW (raw 24 atomicity of [11*] preserved per INTRINSIC-CONSTRAINT-FOUNDATION-ATOMICITY: foundation entries carry only <-, never -> — adding <->/-| does not violate that asymmetry IF [11*] entries are excluded from <-> at adoption time)".
  axis_F_value = "HIGH (4 prose uses of <-> + ~30 latent demand; -| addresses the entire R34/R35/R36 falsification family with no token currently)".
  axis_F_third_proposal_weighted = "->[w] suffix proposed (rank_3); K stays at 8 — backward-compatible; DEFER until <->/-| land".

  axis_G_status = "IN-FLIGHT (parallel sub-agent body-field evolution — vocabulary: confidence/verified/decay) — NOT YET ON DISK; synthesis below is PROVISIONAL pending arrival".
  axis_G_provisional_top_recommendation = "(pending) — most likely candidate is a body-line vocabulary registry (confidence={LOW|MED|HIGH}, verified={YES|NO|PARTIAL}, decay={NONE|t+1|t+k})".
  axis_G_provisional_adoption_cost = "unknown until shard lands — likely 50-200 body-lines touched if confidence/decay become normalized fields".
  axis_G_provisional_risk = "UNKNOWN — body-lines are NOT currently schema-validated, so risk depends on whether axis G proposes promoting them to validated fields".
