  => ""
  => "axis-H (ID-convention .vN + @DATE + @F atlas-id-registry): ORTHOGONAL+ENABLING — axis-H's @F atlas-id-registry block (line 29074-29084) is ITSELF a graph-query target: registry entries become first-class nodes that axis-I closures can walk. Specifically <-* @ @F atlas-id-registry traces every node back to its registered family, which is the natural cross-reference axis-H proposes but cannot express without axis-I"
